      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "A zk circuit (zero-knowledge circuit) is basically a\nmathematical program expressed as constraints. Instead of\n“running code”, you prove that some equations are satisfied\nwithout revealing the secret inputs.\n",
      "fontSize": 21.087524414062482,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "A zk circuit (zero-knowledge circuit) is basically a mathematical program expressed as constraints. Instead of “running code”, you prove that some equations are satisfied without revealing the secret inputs.\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
